Seeking an Engineering Director for our Midrange Vendor Infrastructure Operations; you will work with our outsourced infrastructure partners in delivery of services to the application teams. Platforms supported included: AIX and X86 compute, SAN and NAS Storage, and high availability Stratus compute platforms. You will influence and collaborate with Technology Partners and Product Managers to identify areas of opportunity and risk to our availability and budgets. In addition, you will engage in infrastructure design and migrations to ensure alignment of strategy, architecture, tools/methods and solutions that truly improve the overall experience.
What are the responsibilities of the position?

Actively support our Technology Partners to deliver operations and infrastructure to our application teams
Uplift infrastructure and work with customer applications on migrations/adoption to optimize the environment, align with strategies, and improve availability
Committed to our diverse workforce goals ensuring equal opportunities and growth for all our team members
Develop relations with internal customers to help them through their challenges and ensure our customers partner with the outsourced vendors to support the goals of the company
Oversight of continuous patching to ensure our infrastructure is secure and reliable
Responsible for ensuring availability targets are exceeded for all platforms and customers
Provide support during enterprise level crisis management. Identify, handle, and resolve issues/risks and concerns to leadership team as appropriate. 
Provide 7x24x365 direct support for these portfolios 
Provide the thought-leadership required for Operational Readiness and Service Transition for new/revised services
Provide input into product development organizations to improve product performance, availability, maintainability, resilience, recoverability, and value
Confident in influencing other technical leaders as well as business partnersQualificationsDo you have these qualifications?

BS or MS degree and 3-6 years of work experience in technical delivery or operations
2+ year’s professional management experience providing operations support and architecture delivery
